author: ANTHONY OPPERMANN
title: Houston’s season was meaningful to the end
text: Houston’s season was meaningful to the end Not only did the Astros compile 86 wins, but in the process, they also ended their decade-long playoff drought, clinching a berth in the American League Wild Card game with the Texas Rangers’ 9-2 win over the Los Angeles Angels on the season’s final day. Posted: 12:00 am | Comments (0) AP Sports Pope reminded us about hope, love and humility “Well, I am not Catholic but ...” and “I am not religious but ...” So many conversations during the past week began with those words and then went on to express what a meaningful impact Pope Francis’s visit to our country had on them. Well I am an Episcopalian. And Pope Francis’s words and acts had a profound impact on me.
